Business Description:
Spectral Industries specialisese in Laser-induced Breakdown Spectroscopy (LIBS): An emission spectroscopy technique that provides an elemental fingerprint of a material sample. Real-time monitoring of any type of material is possible with the SPECTRAL Conveyor Belt LIBS sensor. SPECTRAL’s LIBS sensor can be positioned over any conveyor belt. The sensor measures the full atomic chemical composition of the material passing by on the belt. This setup is ideal for mining applications like monitoring the ore grade in mined material in order to separate ore from waste material. Also, the SPECTRAL Conveyer Belt LIBS sensor can be applied for recycling applications to identify materials one wants to sort out.

Benefits of the SPECTRAL Conveyor Belt LIBS sensor: A measurement takes << 1 ms, allowing for measurement rates up to 1000 Hz;
The sensor works with any belt speed; Flexible sensor configuration allows for tunable working distance between sensor and belt; Captures all elements of the periodic table in one measurement; Detection limits below 1 permille (1000 ppm) are possible.
